102 /// DiscoverDependentGlobals - Return a set of GlobalVariables on which \p V ----
103 /// depends. ----
104 static void ----
105 DiscoverDependentGlobals(const Value *V, 0
106 DenseSet &Globals) { ----
107 if (const GlobalVariable *GV = dyn_cast(V)) 0
108 Globals.insert(GV); 0
109 else { ----
110 if (const User *U = dyn_cast(V)) { 0
111 for (unsigned i = 0, e = U->getNumOperands(); i != e; ++i) { 0
112 DiscoverDependentGlobals(U->getOperand(i), Globals); 0
113 } ----
114 } ----
115 } ----
116 } 0
117 ----
118 /// VisitGlobalVariableForEmission - Add \p GV to the list of GlobalVariable ----
119 /// instances to be emitted, but only after any dependents have been added ----
120 /// first.s ----
121 static void ----
122 VisitGlobalVariableForEmission(const GlobalVariable *GV, 0
123 SmallVectorImpl &Order, ----
124 DenseSet &Visited, ----
125 DenseSet &Visiting) { ----
126 // Have we already visited this one? ----
127 if (Visited.count(GV)) 0
128 return; 0
129 ----
130 // Do we have a circular dependency? ----
131 if (!Visiting.insert(GV).second) 0
132 report_fatal_error("Circular dependency found in global variable set"); 0
133 ----
134 // Make sure we visit all dependents first ----
135 DenseSet Others; 0
136 for (unsigned i = 0, e = GV->getNumOperands(); i != e; ++i) 0
137 DiscoverDependentGlobals(GV->getOperand(i), Others); 0
138 ----
139 for (const GlobalVariable *GV : Others) 0
140 VisitGlobalVariableForEmission(GV, Order, Visited, Visiting); 0
141 ----
142 // Now we can visit ourself ----
143 Order.push_back(GV); 0
144 Visited.insert(GV); 0
145 Visiting.erase(GV); 0
146 } 0

151 ----

153 lowerToMCInst(MI, Inst); 0
154 EmitToStreamer(*OutStreamer, Inst); 0
155 } 0

157 // Handle symbol backtracking for targets that do not support image handles ----
158 bool NVPTXAsmPrinter::lowerImageHandleOperand(const MachineInstr *MI, 0
159 unsigned OpNo, MCOperand &MCOp) { ----
160 const MachineOperand &MO = MI->getOperand(OpNo); 0
161 const MCInstrDesc &MCID = MI->getDesc(); 0
162 ----
163 if (MCID.TSFlags & NVPTXII::IsTexFlag) { 0
164 // This is a texture fetch, so operand 4 is a texref and operand 5 is ----
165 // a samplerref ----
166 if (OpNo == 4 && MO.isImm()) { 0
167 lowerImageHandleSymbol(MO.getImm(), MCOp); 0
168 return true; 0
169 } ----
170 if (OpNo == 5 && MO.isImm() && !(MCID.TSFlags & NVPTXII::IsTexModeUnifiedFlag)) { 0
171 lowerImageHandleSymbol(MO.getImm(), MCOp); 0
172 return true; 0
173 } ----
174 ----
175 return false; 0
176 } else if (MCID.TSFlags & NVPTXII::IsSuldMask) { 0
177 unsigned VecSize = 0
178 1 << (((MCID.TSFlags & NVPTXII::IsSuldMask) >> NVPTXII::IsSuldShift) - 1); 0
179 ----
180 // For a surface load of vector size N, the Nth operand will be the surfref ----
181 if (OpNo == VecSize && MO.isImm()) { 0
182 lowerImageHandleSymbol(MO.getImm(), MCOp); 0
183 return true; 0
184 } ----
185 ----
186 return false; 0
187 } else if (MCID.TSFlags & NVPTXII::IsSustFlag) { 0
188 // This is a surface store, so operand 0 is a surfref ----
189 if (OpNo == 0 && MO.isImm()) { 0
190 lowerImageHandleSymbol(MO.getImm(), MCOp); 0
191 return true; 0
192 } ----
193 ----
194 return false; 0
195 } else if (MCID.TSFlags & NVPTXII::IsSurfTexQueryFlag) { 0
196 // This is a query, so operand 1 is a surfref/texref ----
197 if (OpNo == 1 && MO.isImm()) { 0
198 lowerImageHandleSymbol(MO.getImm(), MCOp); 0
199 return true; 0
200 } ----
201 ----
202 return false; 0
203 } ----
204 ----
205 return false; 0
206 } ----

218 void NVPTXAsmPrinter::lowerToMCInst(const MachineInstr *MI, MCInst &OutMI) { 0
219 OutMI.setOpcode(MI->getOpcode()); 0
220 // Special: Do not mangle symbol operand of CALL_PROTOTYPE ----
221 if (MI->getOpcode() == NVPTX::CALL_PROTOTYPE) { 0
222 const MachineOperand &MO = MI->getOperand(0); 0
223 OutMI.addOperand(GetSymbolRef( 0
224 OutContext.getOrCreateSymbol(Twine(MO.getSymbolName())))); 0
225 return; 0
226 } ----
227 ----
228 const NVPTXSubtarget &STI = MI->getMF()->getSubtarget(); 0
229 for (unsigned i = 0, e = MI->getNumOperands(); i != e; ++i) { 0
230 const MachineOperand &MO = MI->getOperand(i); 0
231 ----
232 MCOperand MCOp; 0
233 if (!STI.hasImageHandles()) { 0
234 if (lowerImageHandleOperand(MI, i, MCOp)) { 0
235 OutMI.addOperand(MCOp); 0
236 continue; 0
237 } ----
238 } ----
239 ----
240 if (lowerOperand(MO, MCOp)) 0
241 OutMI.addOperand(MCOp); 0
242 } ----
243 } ----
244 ----
245 bool NVPTXAsmPrinter::lowerOperand(const MachineOperand &MO, 0
246 MCOperand &MCOp) { ----
247 switch (MO.getType()) { 0
248 default: llvm_unreachable("unknown operand type"); 0
249 case MachineOperand::MO_Register: 0
250 MCOp = MCOperand::createReg(encodeVirtualRegister(MO.getReg())); 0
251 break; 0
252 case MachineOperand::MO_Immediate: 0
253 MCOp = MCOperand::createImm(MO.getImm()); 0
254 break; 0
255 case MachineOperand::MO_MachineBasicBlock: 0
256 MCOp = MCOperand::createExpr(MCSymbolRefExpr::create( 0
257 MO.getMBB()->getSymbol(), OutContext)); 0
258 break; 0
259 case MachineOperand::MO_ExternalSymbol: 0
260 MCOp = GetSymbolRef(GetExternalSymbolSymbol(MO.getSymbolName())); 0
261 break; 0
262 case MachineOperand::MO_GlobalAddress: 0
263 MCOp = GetSymbolRef(getSymbol(MO.getGlobal())); 0
264 break; 0
265 case MachineOperand::MO_FPImmediate: { 0
266 const ConstantFP *Cnt = MO.getFPImm(); 0
267 const APFloat &Val = Cnt->getValueAPF(); 0
268 ----
269 switch (Cnt->getType()->getTypeID()) { 0
270 default: report_fatal_error("Unsupported FP type"); break; 0
271 case Type::HalfTyID: 0
272 MCOp = MCOperand::createExpr( 0
273 NVPTXFloatMCExpr::createConstantFPHalf(Val, OutContext)); 0
274 break; 0
275 case Type::BFloatTyID: 0
276 MCOp = MCOperand::createExpr( 0
277 NVPTXFloatMCExpr::createConstantBFPHalf(Val, OutContext)); 0
278 break; 0
279 case Type::FloatTyID: 0
280 MCOp = MCOperand::createExpr( 0
281 NVPTXFloatMCExpr::createConstantFPSingle(Val, OutContext)); 0
282 break; 0
283 case Type::DoubleTyID: 0
284 MCOp = MCOperand::createExpr( 0
285 NVPTXFloatMCExpr::createConstantFPDouble(Val, OutContext)); 0
286 break; 0
287 } ----
288 break; 0
289 } ----
290 } ----
291 return true; 0
292 } ----
293 ----
294 unsigned NVPTXAsmPrinter::encodeVirtualRegister(unsigned Reg) { 0
295 if (Register::isVirtualRegister(Reg)) { 0
296 const TargetRegisterClass *RC = MRI->getRegClass(Reg); 0
297 ----
298 DenseMap &RegMap = VRegMapping[RC]; 0
299 unsigned RegNum = RegMap[Reg]; 0
300 ----
301 // Encode the register class in the upper 4 bits ----
302 // Must be kept in sync with NVPTXInstPrinter::printRegName ----
303 unsigned Ret = 0; 0
304 if (RC == &NVPTX::Int1RegsRegClass) { 0
305 Ret = (1 << 28); 0
306 } else if (RC == &NVPTX::Int16RegsRegClass) { 0
307 Ret = (2 << 28); 0
308 } else if (RC == &NVPTX::Int32RegsRegClass) { 0
309 Ret = (3 << 28); 0
310 } else if (RC == &NVPTX::Int64RegsRegClass) { 0
311 Ret = (4 << 28); 0
312 } else if (RC == &NVPTX::Float32RegsRegClass) { 0
313 Ret = (5 << 28); 0
314 } else if (RC == &NVPTX::Float64RegsRegClass) { 0
315 Ret = (6 << 28); 0
316 } else { ----
317 report_fatal_error("Bad register class"); 0
318 } ----
319 ----
320 // Insert the vreg number ----
321 Ret |= (RegNum & 0x0FFFFFFF); 0
322 return Ret; 0
323 } else { ----
324 // Some special-use registers are actually physical registers. ----
325 // Encode this as the register class ID of 0 and the real register ID. ----
326 return Reg & 0x0FFFFFFF; 0
327 } ----
328 } ----

332 Expr = MCSymbolRefExpr::create(Symbol, MCSymbolRefExpr::VK_None, 0
333 OutContext); ----
334 return MCOperand::createExpr(Expr); 0

337 static bool ShouldPassAsArray(Type *Ty) { 0
338 return Ty->isAggregateType() || Ty->isVectorTy() || Ty->isIntegerTy(128) || 0
339 Ty->isHalfTy() || Ty->isBFloatTy(); 0
340 } ----

342 void NVPTXAsmPrinter::printReturnValStr(const Function *F, raw_ostream &O) { 0
343 const DataLayout &DL = getDataLayout(); 0
344 const NVPTXSubtarget &STI = TM.getSubtarget(*F); 0
345 const auto *TLI = cast(STI.getTargetLowering()); 0
346 ----
347 Type *Ty = F->getReturnType(); 0
348 ----
349 bool isABI = (STI.getSmVersion() >= 20); 0
350 ----
351 if (Ty->getTypeID() == Type::VoidTyID) 0
352 return; 0
353 O << " ("; 0
354 ----
355 if (isABI) { 0
356 if ((Ty->isFloatingPointTy() || Ty->isIntegerTy()) && 0
357 !ShouldPassAsArray(Ty)) { 0
358 unsigned size = 0; 0
359 if (auto *ITy = dyn_cast(Ty)) { 0
360 size = ITy->getBitWidth(); 0
361 } else { ----
362 assert(Ty->isFloatingPointTy() && "Floating point type expected here"); 0
363 size = Ty->getPrimitiveSizeInBits(); 0
364 } ----
365 size = promoteScalarArgumentSize(size); 0
366 O << ".param .b" << size << " func_retval0"; 0
367 } else if (isa(Ty)) { 0
368 O << ".param .b" << TLI->getPointerTy(DL).getSizeInBits() 0
369 << " func_retval0"; 0
370 } else if (ShouldPassAsArray(Ty)) { 0
371 unsigned totalsz = DL.getTypeAllocSize(Ty); 0
372 unsigned retAlignment = 0; 0
373 if (!getAlign(*F, 0, retAlignment)) 0
374 retAlignment = TLI->getFunctionParamOptimizedAlign(F, Ty, DL).value(); 0
375 O << ".param .align " << retAlignment << " .b8 func_retval0[" << totalsz 0
376 << "]"; 0
377 } else ----
378 llvm_unreachable("Unknown return type"); 0
379 } else { ----
380 SmallVector vtparts; 0
381 ComputeValueVTs(*TLI, DL, Ty, vtparts); 0
382 unsigned idx = 0; 0
383 for (unsigned i = 0, e = vtparts.size(); i != e; ++i) { 0
384 unsigned elems = 1; 0
385 EVT elemtype = vtparts[i]; 0
386 if (vtparts[i].isVector()) { 0
387 elems = vtparts[i].getVectorNumElements(); 0
388 elemtype = vtparts[i].getVectorElementType(); 0
389 } ----
390 ----
391 for (unsigned j = 0, je = elems; j != je; ++j) { 0
392 unsigned sz = elemtype.getSizeInBits(); 0
393 if (elemtype.isInteger()) 0
394 sz = promoteScalarArgumentSize(sz); 0
395 O << ".reg .b" << sz << " func_retval" << idx; 0
396 if (j < je - 1) 0
397 O << ", "; 0
398 ++idx; 0
399 } ----
400 if (i < e - 1) 0
401 O << ", "; 0
402 } ----
403 } 0
404 O << ") "; 0
405 } ----

409 const Function &F = MF.getFunction(); 0
410 printReturnValStr(&F, O); 0

413 // Return true if MBB is the header of a loop marked with ----
414 // llvm.loop.unroll.disable or llvm.loop.unroll.count=1. ----
415 bool NVPTXAsmPrinter::isLoopHeaderOfNoUnroll( 0
416 const MachineBasicBlock &MBB) const { ----
417 MachineLoopInfo &LI = getAnalysis(); 0
418 // We insert .pragma "nounroll" only to the loop header. ----
419 if (!LI.isLoopHeader(&MBB)) 0
420 return false; 0
421 ----
422 // llvm.loop.unroll.disable is marked on the back edges of a loop. Therefore, ----
423 // we iterate through each back edge of the loop with header MBB, and check ----
424 // whether its metadata contains llvm.loop.unroll.disable. ----
425 for (const MachineBasicBlock *PMBB : MBB.predecessors()) { 0
426 if (LI.getLoopFor(PMBB) != LI.getLoopFor(&MBB)) { 0
427 // Edges from other loops to MBB are not back edges. ----
428 continue; 0
429 } ----
430 if (const BasicBlock *PBB = PMBB->getBasicBlock()) { 0
431 if (MDNode *LoopID = 0
432 PBB->getTerminator()->getMetadata(LLVMContext::MD_loop)) { 0
433 if (GetUnrollMetadata(LoopID, "llvm.loop.unroll.disable")) 0
434 return true; 0
435 if (MDNode *UnrollCountMD = 0
436 GetUnrollMetadata(LoopID, "llvm.loop.unroll.count")) { 0
437 if (mdconst::extract(UnrollCountMD->getOperand(1)) 0
438 ->isOne()) 0
439 return true; 0
440 } ----
441 } ----
442 } ----
443 } ----
444 return false; 0
445 } ----
446 ----
447 void NVPTXAsmPrinter::emitBasicBlockStart(const MachineBasicBlock &MBB) { 0
448 AsmPrinter::emitBasicBlockStart(MBB); 0
449 if (isLoopHeaderOfNoUnroll(MBB)) 0
450 OutStreamer->emitRawText(StringRef("\t.pragma \"nounroll\";\n")); 0
451 } 0

453 void NVPTXAsmPrinter::emitFunctionEntryLabel() { 0
454 SmallString<128> Str; 0
455 raw_svector_ostream O(Str); 0
456 ----
457 if (!GlobalsEmitted) { 0
458 emitGlobals(*MF->getFunction().getParent()); 0
459 GlobalsEmitted = true; 0
460 } ----
461 ----
462 // Set up ----
463 MRI = &MF->getRegInfo(); 0
464 F = &MF->getFunction(); 0
465 emitLinkageDirective(F, O); 0
466 if (isKernelFunction(*F)) 0
467 O << ".entry "; 0
468 else { ----
469 O << ".func "; 0
470 printReturnValStr(*MF, O); 0
471 } ----
472 ----
473 CurrentFnSym->print(O, MAI); 0
474 ----
475 emitFunctionParamList(F, O); 0
476 O << "\n"; 0
477 ----
478 if (isKernelFunction(*F)) 0
479 emitKernelFunctionDirectives(*F, O); 0
480 ----

482 O << ".noreturn"; 0
483 ----
484 OutStreamer->emitRawText(O.str()); 0
485 ----
486 VRegMapping.clear(); 0
487 // Emit open brace for function body. ----
488 OutStreamer->emitRawText(StringRef("{\n")); 0
489 setAndEmitFunctionVirtualRegisters(*MF); 0
490 // Emit initial .loc debug directive for correct relocation symbol data. ----
491 if (MMI && MMI->hasDebugInfo()) 0
492 emitInitialRawDwarfLocDirective(*MF); 0
493 } 0

535 ----
536 void NVPTXAsmPrinter::emitKernelFunctionDirectives(const Function &F, 0
537 raw_ostream &O) const { ----
538 // If the NVVM IR has some of reqntid* specified, then output ----
539 // the reqntid directive, and set the unspecified ones to 1. ----
540 // If none of reqntid* is specified, don't output reqntid directive. ----
541 unsigned reqntidx, reqntidy, reqntidz; ----
542 bool specified = false; 0
543 if (!getReqNTIDx(F, reqntidx)) 0
544 reqntidx = 1; 0
545 else ----
546 specified = true; 0
547 if (!getReqNTIDy(F, reqntidy)) 0
548 reqntidy = 1; 0
549 else ----
550 specified = true; 0
551 if (!getReqNTIDz(F, reqntidz)) 0
552 reqntidz = 1; 0
553 else ----
554 specified = true; 0
555 ----
556 if (specified) 0
557 O << ".reqntid " << reqntidx << ", " << reqntidy << ", " << reqntidz 0
558 << "\n"; 0
559 ----
560 // If the NVVM IR has some of maxntid* specified, then output ----
561 // the maxntid directive, and set the unspecified ones to 1. ----
562 // If none of maxntid* is specified, don't output maxntid directive. ----
563 unsigned maxntidx, maxntidy, maxntidz; ----
564 specified = false; 0
565 if (!getMaxNTIDx(F, maxntidx)) 0
566 maxntidx = 1; 0
567 else ----
568 specified = true; 0
569 if (!getMaxNTIDy(F, maxntidy)) 0
570 maxntidy = 1; 0
571 else ----
572 specified = true; 0
573 if (!getMaxNTIDz(F, maxntidz)) 0
574 maxntidz = 1; 0
575 else ----
576 specified = true; 0
577 ----
578 if (specified) 0
579 O << ".maxntid " << maxntidx << ", " << maxntidy << ", " << maxntidz 0
580 << "\n"; 0
581 ----
582 unsigned mincta; ----
583 if (getMinCTASm(F, mincta)) 0
584 O << ".minnctapersm " << mincta << "\n"; 0
585 ----
586 unsigned maxnreg; ----
587 if (getMaxNReg(F, maxnreg)) 0
588 O << ".maxnreg " << maxnreg << "\n"; 0
589 } 0

591 std::string ----
592 NVPTXAsmPrinter::getVirtualRegisterName(unsigned Reg) const { 0
593 const TargetRegisterClass *RC = MRI->getRegClass(Reg); 0
594 ----
595 std::string Name; 0
596 raw_string_ostream NameStr(Name); 0
597 ----
598 VRegRCMap::const_iterator I = VRegMapping.find(RC); 0
599 assert(I != VRegMapping.end() && "Bad register class"); 0
600 const DenseMap &RegMap = I->second; 0
601 ----
602 VRegMap::const_iterator VI = RegMap.find(Reg); 0
603 assert(VI != RegMap.end() && "Bad virtual register"); 0
604 unsigned MappedVR = VI->second; 0
605 ----
606 NameStr << getNVPTXRegClassStr(RC) << MappedVR; 0
607 ----
608 NameStr.flush(); 0
609 return Name; 0
610 } 0
611 ----
612 void NVPTXAsmPrinter::emitVirtualRegister(unsigned int vr, 0
613 raw_ostream &O) { ----
614 O << getVirtualRegisterName(vr); 0
615 } 0
616 ----
617 void NVPTXAsmPrinter::emitDeclaration(const Function *F, raw_ostream &O) { 0
618 emitLinkageDirective(F, O); 0
619 if (isKernelFunction(*F)) 0
620 O << ".entry "; 0
621 else ----
622 O << ".func "; 0
623 printReturnValStr(F, O); 0
624 getSymbol(F)->print(O, MAI); 0
625 O << "\n"; 0
626 emitFunctionParamList(F, O); 0
627 O << "\n"; 0
628 if (shouldEmitPTXNoReturn(F, TM)) 0
629 O << ".noreturn"; 0
630 O << ";\n"; 0
631 } 0
632 ----
633 static bool usedInGlobalVarDef(const Constant *C) { 0
634 if (!C) 0
635 return false; 0
636 ----
637 if (const GlobalVariable *GV = dyn_cast(C)) { 0
638 return GV->getName() != "llvm.used"; 0
639 } ----
640 ----
641 for (const User *U : C->users()) 0
642 if (const Constant *C = dyn_cast(U)) 0
643 if (usedInGlobalVarDef(C)) 0
644 return true; 0
645 ----
646 return false; 0
647 } ----
648 ----
649 static bool usedInOneFunc(const User *U, Function const *&oneFunc) { 0
650 if (const GlobalVariable *othergv = dyn_cast(U)) { 0
651 if (othergv->getName() == "llvm.used") 0
652 return true; 0
653 } ----
654 ----
655 if (const Instruction *instr = dyn_cast(U)) { 0
656 if (instr->getParent() && instr->getParent()->getParent()) { 0
657 const Function *curFunc = instr->getParent()->getParent(); 0
658 if (oneFunc && (curFunc != oneFunc)) 0
659 return false; 0
660 oneFunc = curFunc; 0
661 return true; 0
662 } else ----
663 return false; 0
664 } ----
665 ----
666 for (const User *UU : U->users()) 0
667 if (!usedInOneFunc(UU, oneFunc)) 0
668 return false; 0
669 ----
670 return true; 0
671 } ----
672 ----
673 /* Find out if a global variable can be demoted to local scope. ----
674 * Currently, this is valid for CUDA shared variables, which have local ----
675 * scope and global lifetime. So the conditions to check are : ----
676 * 1. Is the global variable in shared address space? ----
677 * 2. Does it have internal linkage? ----
678 * 3. Is the global variable referenced only in one function? ----
679 */ ----
680 static bool canDemoteGlobalVar(const GlobalVariable *gv, Function const *&f) { 0
681 if (!gv->hasInternalLinkage()) 0
682 return false; 0
683 PointerType *Pty = gv->getType(); 0
684 if (Pty->getAddressSpace() != ADDRESS_SPACE_SHARED) 0
685 return false; 0
686 ----
687 const Function *oneFunc = nullptr; 0
688 ----
689 bool flag = usedInOneFunc(gv, oneFunc); 0
690 if (!flag) 0
691 return false; 0
692 if (!oneFunc) 0
693 return false; 0
694 f = oneFunc; 0
695 return true; 0
696 } ----
697 ----
698 static bool useFuncSeen(const Constant *C, 0
699 DenseMap &seenMap) { ----
700 for (const User *U : C->users()) { 0
701 if (const Constant *cu = dyn_cast(U)) { 0
702 if (useFuncSeen(cu, seenMap)) 0
703 return true; 0
704 } else if (const Instruction *I = dyn_cast(U)) { 0
705 const BasicBlock *bb = I->getParent(); 0
706 if (!bb) 0
707 continue; 0
708 const Function *caller = bb->getParent(); 0
709 if (!caller) 0
710 continue; 0
711 if (seenMap.contains(caller)) 0
712 return true; 0
713 } ----
714 } ----
715 return false; 0
716 } ----
717 ----
718 void NVPTXAsmPrinter::emitDeclarations(const Module &M, raw_ostream &O) { 0
719 DenseMap seenMap; 0
720 for (const Function &F : M) { 0
721 if (F.getAttributes().hasFnAttr("nvptx-libcall-callee")) { 0
722 emitDeclaration(&F, O); 0
723 continue; 0
724 } ----
725 ----
726 if (F.isDeclaration()) { 0
727 if (F.use_empty()) 0
728 continue; 0
729 if (F.getIntrinsicID()) 0
730 continue; 0
731 emitDeclaration(&F, O); 0
732 continue; 0
733 } ----
734 for (const User *U : F.users()) { 0
735 if (const Constant *C = dyn_cast(U)) { 0
736 if (usedInGlobalVarDef(C)) { 0
737 // The use is in the initialization of a global variable ----
738 // that is a function pointer, so print a declaration ----
739 // for the original function ----
740 emitDeclaration(&F, O); 0
741 break; 0
742 } ----
743 // Emit a declaration of this function if the function that ----
744 // uses this constant expr has already been seen. ----
745 if (useFuncSeen(C, seenMap)) { 0
746 emitDeclaration(&F, O); 0
747 break; 0
748 } ----
749 } ----
750 ----
751 if (!isa(U)) 0
752 continue; 0
753 const Instruction *instr = cast(U); 0
754 const BasicBlock *bb = instr->getParent(); 0
755 if (!bb) 0
756 continue; 0
757 const Function *caller = bb->getParent(); 0
758 if (!caller) 0
759 continue; 0
760 ----
761 // If a caller has already been seen, then the caller is ----
762 // appearing in the module before the callee. so print out ----
763 // a declaration for the callee. ----
764 if (seenMap.contains(caller)) { 0
765 emitDeclaration(&F, O); 0
766 break; 0
767 } ----
768 } ----
769 seenMap[&F] = true; 0
770 } ----
771 } 0
772 ----
773 static bool isEmptyXXStructor(GlobalVariable *GV) { 0
774 if (!GV) return true; 0
775 const ConstantArray *InitList = dyn_cast(GV->getInitializer()); 0
776 if (!InitList) return true; // Not an array; we don't know how to parse. 0
777 return InitList->getNumOperands() == 0; 0
778 } ----
779 ----
780 void NVPTXAsmPrinter::emitStartOfAsmFile(Module &M) { 0
781 // Construct a default subtarget off of the TargetMachine defaults. The ----
782 // rest of NVPTX isn't friendly to change subtargets per function and ----
783 // so the default TargetMachine will have all of the options. ----
784 const NVPTXTargetMachine &NTM = static_cast(TM); 0
785 const auto* STI = static_cast(NTM.getSubtargetImpl()); 0
786 SmallString<128> Str1; 0
787 raw_svector_ostream OS1(Str1); 0
788 ----
789 // Emit header before any dwarf directives are emitted below. ----
790 emitHeader(M, OS1, *STI); 0
791 OutStreamer->emitRawText(OS1.str()); 0
792 } 0
793 ----
794 bool NVPTXAsmPrinter::doInitialization(Module &M) { 0
795 const NVPTXTargetMachine &NTM = static_cast(TM); 0
796 const NVPTXSubtarget &STI = ----
797 *static_cast(NTM.getSubtargetImpl()); 0
798 if (M.alias_size() && (STI.getPTXVersion() < 63 || STI.getSmVersion() < 30)) 0
799 report_fatal_error(".alias requires PTX version >= 6.3 and sm_30"); 0
800 ----
801 if (!isEmptyXXStructor(M.getNamedGlobal("llvm.global_ctors")) && 0
802 !LowerCtorDtor) { 0
803 report_fatal_error( 0
804 "Module has a nontrivial global ctor, which NVPTX does not support."); ----
805 return true; // error ----
806 } ----
807 if (!isEmptyXXStructor(M.getNamedGlobal("llvm.global_dtors")) && 0
808 !LowerCtorDtor) { 0
809 report_fatal_error( 0
810 "Module has a nontrivial global dtor, which NVPTX does not support."); ----
811 return true; // error ----
812 } ----
813 ----
814 // We need to call the parent's one explicitly. ----
815 bool Result = AsmPrinter::doInitialization(M); 0
816 ----
817 GlobalsEmitted = false; 0
818 ----
819 return Result; 0
820 } ----
821 ----
822 void NVPTXAsmPrinter::emitGlobals(const Module &M) { 0
823 SmallString<128> Str2; 0
824 raw_svector_ostream OS2(Str2); 0
825 ----
826 emitDeclarations(M, OS2); 0
827 ----
828 // As ptxas does not support forward references of globals, we need to first ----
829 // sort the list of module-level globals in def-use order. We visit each ----
830 // global variable in order, and ensure that we emit it *after* its dependent ----
831 // globals. We use a little extra memory maintaining both a set and a list to ----
832 // have fast searches while maintaining a strict ordering. ----
833 SmallVector Globals; 0
834 DenseSet GVVisited; 0
835 DenseSet GVVisiting; 0
836 ----
837 // Visit each global variable, in order ----
838 for (const GlobalVariable &I : M.globals()) 0
839 VisitGlobalVariableForEmission(&I, Globals, GVVisited, GVVisiting); 0
840 ----
841 assert(GVVisited.size() == M.global_size() && "Missed a global variable"); 0
842 assert(GVVisiting.size() == 0 && "Did not fully process a global variable"); 0
843 ----
844 const NVPTXTargetMachine &NTM = static_cast(TM); 0
845 const NVPTXSubtarget &STI = ----
846 *static_cast(NTM.getSubtargetImpl()); 0
847 ----
848 // Print out module-level global variables in proper order ----
849 for (unsigned i = 0, e = Globals.size(); i != e; ++i) 0
850 printModuleLevelGV(Globals[i], OS2, /*processDemoted=*/false, STI); 0
851 ----
852 OS2 << '\n'; 0
853 ----
854 OutStreamer->emitRawText(OS2.str()); 0
855 } 0
856 ----
857 void NVPTXAsmPrinter::emitGlobalAlias(const Module &M, const GlobalAlias &GA) { 0
858 SmallString<128> Str; 0
859 raw_svector_ostream OS(Str); 0
860 ----
861 MCSymbol *Name = getSymbol(&GA); 0
862 const Function *F = dyn_cast(GA.getAliasee()); 0
863 if (!F || isKernelFunction(*F)) 0
864 report_fatal_error("NVPTX aliasee must be a non-kernel function"); 0
865 ----
866 if (GA.hasLinkOnceLinkage() || GA.hasWeakLinkage() || 0
867 GA.hasAvailableExternallyLinkage() || GA.hasCommonLinkage()) 0
868 report_fatal_error("NVPTX aliasee must not be '.weak'"); 0
869 ----
870 OS << "\n"; 0
871 emitLinkageDirective(F, OS); 0
872 OS << ".func "; 0
873 printReturnValStr(F, OS); 0
874 OS << Name->getName(); 0
875 emitFunctionParamList(F, OS); 0
876 if (shouldEmitPTXNoReturn(F, TM)) 0
877 OS << "\n.noreturn"; 0
878 OS << ";\n"; 0
879 ----
880 OS << ".alias " << Name->getName() << ", " << F->getName() << ";\n"; 0
881 ----
882 OutStreamer->emitRawText(OS.str()); 0
883 } 0
884 ----
885 void NVPTXAsmPrinter::emitHeader(Module &M, raw_ostream &O, 0
886 const NVPTXSubtarget &STI) { ----
887 O << "//\n"; 0
888 O << "// Generated by LLVM NVPTX Back-End\n"; 0
889 O << "//\n"; 0
890 O << "\n"; 0
891 ----
892 unsigned PTXVersion = STI.getPTXVersion(); 0
893 O << ".version " << (PTXVersion / 10) << "." << (PTXVersion % 10) << "\n"; 0
894 ----
895 O << ".target "; 0
896 O << STI.getTargetName(); 0
897 ----
898 const NVPTXTargetMachine &NTM = static_cast(TM); 0
899 if (NTM.getDrvInterface() == NVPTX::NVCL) 0
900 O << ", texmode_independent"; 0
901 ----
902 bool HasFullDebugInfo = false; 0
903 for (DICompileUnit *CU : M.debug_compile_units()) { 0
904 switch(CU->getEmissionKind()) { 0
905 case DICompileUnit::NoDebug: 0
906 case DICompileUnit::DebugDirectivesOnly: ----
907 break; 0
908 case DICompileUnit::LineTablesOnly: 0
909 case DICompileUnit::FullDebug: ----
910 HasFullDebugInfo = true; 0
911 break; 0
912 } ----
913 if (HasFullDebugInfo) 0
914 break; 0
915 } ----
916 if (MMI && MMI->hasDebugInfo() && HasFullDebugInfo) 0
917 O << ", debug"; 0
918 ----
919 O << "\n"; 0
920 ----
921 O << ".address_size "; 0
922 if (NTM.is64Bit()) 0
923 O << "64"; 0
924 else ----
925 O << "32"; 0
926 O << "\n"; 0
927 ----
928 O << "\n"; 0
929 } 0
930 ----
931 bool NVPTXAsmPrinter::doFinalization(Module &M) { 0
932 bool HasDebugInfo = MMI && MMI->hasDebugInfo(); 0
933 ----
934 // If we did not emit any functions, then the global declarations have not ----
935 // yet been emitted. ----
936 if (!GlobalsEmitted) { 0
937 emitGlobals(M); 0
938 GlobalsEmitted = true; 0
939 } ----
940 ----
941 // If we have any aliases we emit them at the end. ----
942 SmallVector AliasesToRemove; 0
943 for (GlobalAlias &Alias : M.aliases()) { 0
944 emitGlobalAlias(M, Alias); 0
945 AliasesToRemove.push_back(&Alias); 0
946 } ----
947 ----
948 for (GlobalAlias *A : AliasesToRemove) 0
949 A->eraseFromParent(); 0
950 ----
951 // call doFinalization ----
952 bool ret = AsmPrinter::doFinalization(M); 0
953 ----
954 clearAnnotationCache(&M); 0
955 ----
956 auto *TS = ----
957 static_cast(OutStreamer->getTargetStreamer()); 0
958 // Close the last emitted section ----
959 if (HasDebugInfo) { 0
960 TS->closeLastSection(); 0
961 // Emit empty .debug_loc section for better support of the empty files. ----
962 OutStreamer->emitRawText("\t.section\t.debug_loc\t{\t}"); 0
963 } ----
964 ----
965 // Output last DWARF .file directives, if any. ----
966 TS->outputDwarfFileDirectives(); 0
967 ----
968 return ret; 0
969 } 0
970 ----
971 // This function emits appropriate linkage directives for ----
972 // functions and global variables. ----
973 // ----
974 // extern function declaration -> .extern ----
975 // extern function definition -> .visible ----
976 // external global variable with init -> .visible ----
977 // external without init -> .extern ----
978 // appending -> not allowed, assert. ----
979 // for any linkage other than ----
980 // internal, private, linker_private, ----
981 // linker_private_weak, linker_private_weak_def_auto, ----
982 // we emit -> .weak. ----
983 ----
984 void NVPTXAsmPrinter::emitLinkageDirective(const GlobalValue *V, 0
985 raw_ostream &O) { ----
986 if (static_cast(TM).getDrvInterface() == NVPTX::CUDA) { 0
987 if (V->hasExternalLinkage()) { 0
988 if (isa(V)) { 0
989 const GlobalVariable *GVar = cast(V); 0
990 if (GVar) { 0
991 if (GVar->hasInitializer()) 0
992 O << ".visible "; 0
993 else ----
994 O << ".extern "; 0
995 } ----
996 } else if (V->isDeclaration()) 0
997 O << ".extern "; 0
998 else ----
999 O << ".visible "; 0
1000 } else if (V->hasAppendingLinkage()) { 0
1001 std::string msg; 0
1002 msg.append("Error: "); 0
1003 msg.append("Symbol "); 0
1004 if (V->hasName()) 0
1005 msg.append(std::string(V->getName())); 0
1006 msg.append("has unsupported appending linkage type"); 0
1007 llvm_unreachable(msg.c_str()); 0
1008 } else if (!V->hasInternalLinkage() && 0
1009 !V->hasPrivateLinkage()) { 0
1010 O << ".weak "; 0
1011 } ----
1012 } ----
1013 } 0
1014 ----
1015 void NVPTXAsmPrinter::printModuleLevelGV(const GlobalVariable *GVar, 0
1016 raw_ostream &O, bool processDemoted, ----
1017 const NVPTXSubtarget &STI) { ----
1018 // Skip meta data ----
1019 if (GVar->hasSection()) { 0
1020 if (GVar->getSection() == "llvm.metadata") 0
1021 return; 0
1022 } ----
1023 ----
1024 // Skip LLVM intrinsic global variables ----
1025 if (GVar->getName().startswith("llvm.") || 0
1026 GVar->getName().startswith("nvvm.")) 0
1027 return; 0
1028 ----
1029 const DataLayout &DL = getDataLayout(); 0
1030 ----
1031 // GlobalVariables are always constant pointers themselves. ----
1032 PointerType *PTy = GVar->getType(); 0
1033 Type *ETy = GVar->getValueType(); 0
1034 ----
1035 if (GVar->hasExternalLinkage()) { 0
1036 if (GVar->hasInitializer()) 0
1037 O << ".visible "; 0
1038 else ----
1039 O << ".extern "; 0
1040 } else if (GVar->hasLinkOnceLinkage() || GVar->hasWeakLinkage() || 0
1041 GVar->hasAvailableExternallyLinkage() || 0
1042 GVar->hasCommonLinkage()) { 0
1043 O << ".weak "; 0
1044 } ----
1045 ----
1046 if (isTexture(*GVar)) { 0
1047 O << ".global .texref " << getTextureName(*GVar) << ";\n"; 0
1048 return; 0
1049 } ----
1050 ----
1051 if (isSurface(*GVar)) { 0
1052 O << ".global .surfref " << getSurfaceName(*GVar) << ";\n"; 0
1053 return; 0
1054 } ----
1055 ----
1056 if (GVar->isDeclaration()) { 0
1057 // (extern) declarations, no definition or initializer ----
1058 // Currently the only known declaration is for an automatic __local ----
1059 // (.shared) promoted to global. ----
1060 emitPTXGlobalVariable(GVar, O, STI); 0
1061 O << ";\n"; 0
1062 return; 0
1063 } ----
1064 ----
1065 if (isSampler(*GVar)) { 0
1066 O << ".global .samplerref " << getSamplerName(*GVar); 0
1067 ----
1068 const Constant *Initializer = nullptr; 0
1069 if (GVar->hasInitializer()) 0
1070 Initializer = GVar->getInitializer(); 0
1071 const ConstantInt *CI = nullptr; 0
1072 if (Initializer) 0
1073 CI = dyn_cast(Initializer); 0
1074 if (CI) { 0
1075 unsigned sample = CI->getZExtValue(); 0
1076 ----
1077 O << " = { "; 0
1078 ----
1079 for (int i = 0, 0
1080 addr = ((sample & __CLK_ADDRESS_MASK) >> __CLK_ADDRESS_BASE); 0
1081 i < 3; i++) { 0
1082 O << "addr_mode_" << i << " = "; 0
1083 switch (addr) { 0
1084 case 0: 0
1085 O << "wrap"; 0
1086 break; 0
1087 case 1: 0
1088 O << "clamp_to_border"; 0
1089 break; 0
1090 case 2: 0
1091 O << "clamp_to_edge"; 0
1092 break; 0
1093 case 3: 0
1094 O << "wrap"; 0
1095 break; 0
1096 case 4: 0
1097 O << "mirror"; 0
1098 break; 0
1099 } ----
1100 O << ", "; 0
1101 } ----
1102 O << "filter_mode = "; 0
1103 switch ((sample & __CLK_FILTER_MASK) >> __CLK_FILTER_BASE) { 0
1104 case 0: 0
1105 O << "nearest"; 0
1106 break; 0
1107 case 1: 0
1108 O << "linear"; 0
1109 break; 0
1110 case 2: 0
1111 llvm_unreachable("Anisotropic filtering is not supported"); 0
1112 default: 0
1113 O << "nearest"; 0
1114 break; 0
1115 } ----
1116 if (!((sample & __CLK_NORMALIZED_MASK) >> __CLK_NORMALIZED_BASE)) { 0
1117 O << ", force_unnormalized_coords = 1"; 0
1118 } ----
1119 O << " }"; 0
1120 } ----
1121 ----
1122 O << ";\n"; 0
1123 return; 0
1124 } ----
1125 ----
1126 if (GVar->hasPrivateLinkage()) { 0
1127 if (strncmp(GVar->getName().data(), "unrollpragma", 12) == 0) 0
1128 return; 0
1129 ----
1130 // FIXME - need better way (e.g. Metadata) to avoid generating this global ----
1131 if (strncmp(GVar->getName().data(), "filename", 8) == 0) 0
1132 return; 0
1133 if (GVar->use_empty()) 0
1134 return; 0
1135 } ----
1136 ----
1137 const Function *demotedFunc = nullptr; 0
1138 if (!processDemoted && canDemoteGlobalVar(GVar, demotedFunc)) { 0
1139 O << "// " << GVar->getName() << " has been demoted\n"; 0
1140 if (localDecls.find(demotedFunc) != localDecls.end()) 0
1141 localDecls[demotedFunc].push_back(GVar); 0
1142 else { ----
1143 std::vector temp; 0
1144 temp.push_back(GVar); 0
1145 localDecls[demotedFunc] = temp; 0
1146 } 0
1147 return; 0
1148 } ----
1149 ----
1150 O << "."; 0
1151 emitPTXAddressSpace(PTy->getAddressSpace(), O); 0
1152 ----
1153 if (isManaged(*GVar)) { 0
1154 if (STI.getPTXVersion() < 40 || STI.getSmVersion() < 30) { 0
1155 report_fatal_error( 0
1156 ".attribute(.managed) requires PTX version >= 4.0 and sm_30"); ----
1157 } ----
1158 O << " .attribute(.managed)"; 0
1159 } ----
1160 ----
1161 if (MaybeAlign A = GVar->getAlign()) 0
1162 O << " .align " << A->value(); 0
1163 else ----
1164 O << " .align " << (int)DL.getPrefTypeAlign(ETy).value(); 0
1165 ----
1166 if (ETy->isFloatingPointTy() || ETy->isPointerTy() || 0
1167 (ETy->isIntegerTy() && ETy->getScalarSizeInBits() <= 64)) { 0
1168 O << " ."; 0
1169 // Special case: ABI requires that we use .u8 for predicates ----
1170 if (ETy->isIntegerTy(1)) 0
1171 O << "u8"; 0
1172 else ----
1173 O << getPTXFundamentalTypeStr(ETy, false); 0
1174 O << " "; 0
1175 getSymbol(GVar)->print(O, MAI); 0
1176 ----
1177 // Ptx allows variable initilization only for constant and global state ----
1178 // spaces. ----
1179 if (GVar->hasInitializer()) { 0
1180 if ((PTy->getAddressSpace() == ADDRESS_SPACE_GLOBAL) || 0
1181 (PTy->getAddressSpace() == ADDRESS_SPACE_CONST)) { 0
1182 const Constant *Initializer = GVar->getInitializer(); 0
1183 // 'undef' is treated as there is no value specified. ----
1184 if (!Initializer->isNullValue() && !isa(Initializer)) { 0
1185 O << " = "; 0
1186 printScalarConstant(Initializer, O); 0
1187 } ----
1188 } else { ----
1189 // The frontend adds zero-initializer to device and constant variables ----
1190 // that don't have an initial value, and UndefValue to shared ----
1191 // variables, so skip warning for this case. ----
1192 if (!GVar->getInitializer()->isNullValue() && 0
1193 !isa(GVar->getInitializer())) { 0
1194 report_fatal_error("initial value of '" + GVar->getName() + 0
1195 "' is not allowed in addrspace(" + 0
1196 Twine(PTy->getAddressSpace()) + ")"); 0
1197 } ----
1198 } ----
1199 } ----
1200 } else { ----
1201 uint64_t ElementSize = 0; 0
1202 ----
1203 // Although PTX has direct support for struct type and array type and ----
1204 // LLVM IR is very similar to PTX, the LLVM CodeGen does not support for ----
1205 // targets that support these high level field accesses. Structs, arrays ----
1206 // and vectors are lowered into arrays of bytes. ----
1207 switch (ETy->getTypeID()) { 0
1208 case Type::IntegerTyID: // Integers larger than 64 bits 0
1209 case Type::StructTyID: ----
1210 case Type::ArrayTyID: ----
1211 case Type::FixedVectorTyID: ----
1212 ElementSize = DL.getTypeStoreSize(ETy); 0
1213 // Ptx allows variable initilization only for constant and ----
1214 // global state spaces. ----
1215 if (((PTy->getAddressSpace() == ADDRESS_SPACE_GLOBAL) || 0
1216 (PTy->getAddressSpace() == ADDRESS_SPACE_CONST)) && 0
1217 GVar->hasInitializer()) { 0
1218 const Constant *Initializer = GVar->getInitializer(); 0
1219 if (!isa(Initializer) && !Initializer->isNullValue()) { 0
1220 AggBuffer aggBuffer(ElementSize, *this); 0
1221 bufferAggregateConstant(Initializer, &aggBuffer); 0
1222 if (aggBuffer.numSymbols()) { 0
1223 unsigned int ptrSize = MAI->getCodePointerSize(); 0
1224 if (ElementSize % ptrSize || 0
1225 !aggBuffer.allSymbolsAligned(ptrSize)) { 0
1226 // Print in bytes and use the mask() operator for pointers. ----
1227 if (!STI.hasMaskOperator()) 0
1228 report_fatal_error( 0
1229 "initialized packed aggregate with pointers '" + ----
1230 GVar->getName() + 0
1231 "' requires at least PTX ISA version 7.1"); 0
1232 O << " .u8 "; 0
1233 getSymbol(GVar)->print(O, MAI); 0
1234 O << "[" << ElementSize << "] = {"; 0
1235 aggBuffer.printBytes(O); 0
1236 O << "}"; 0
1237 } else { ----
1238 O << " .u" << ptrSize * 8 << " "; 0
1239 getSymbol(GVar)->print(O, MAI); 0
1240 O << "[" << ElementSize / ptrSize << "] = {"; 0
1241 aggBuffer.printWords(O); 0
1242 O << "}"; 0
1243 } ----
1244 } else { ----
1245 O << " .b8 "; 0
1246 getSymbol(GVar)->print(O, MAI); 0
1247 O << "[" << ElementSize << "] = {"; 0
1248 aggBuffer.printBytes(O); 0
1249 O << "}"; 0
1250 } ----
1251 } else { 0
1252 O << " .b8 "; 0
1253 getSymbol(GVar)->print(O, MAI); 0
1254 if (ElementSize) { 0
1255 O << "["; 0
1256 O << ElementSize; 0
1257 O << "]"; 0
1258 } ----
1259 } ----
1260 } else { ----
1261 O << " .b8 "; 0
1262 getSymbol(GVar)->print(O, MAI); 0
1263 if (ElementSize) { 0
1264 O << "["; 0
1265 O << ElementSize; 0
1266 O << "]"; 0
1267 } ----
1268 } ----
1269 break; 0
1270 default: 0
1271 llvm_unreachable("type not supported yet"); 0
1272 } ----
1273 } ----
1274 O << ";\n"; 0
1275 } ----
1276 ----
1277 void NVPTXAsmPrinter::AggBuffer::printSymbol(unsigned nSym, raw_ostream &os) { 0
1278 const Value *v = Symbols[nSym]; 0
1279 const Value *v0 = SymbolsBeforeStripping[nSym]; 0
1280 if (const GlobalValue *GVar = dyn_cast(v)) { 0
1281 MCSymbol *Name = AP.getSymbol(GVar); 0
1282 PointerType *PTy = dyn_cast(v0->getType()); 0
1283 // Is v0 a generic pointer? ----
1284 bool isGenericPointer = PTy && PTy->getAddressSpace() == 0; 0
1285 if (EmitGeneric && isGenericPointer && !isa(v)) { 0
1286 os << "generic("; 0
1287 Name->print(os, AP.MAI); 0
1288 os << ")"; 0
1289 } else { ----
1290 Name->print(os, AP.MAI); 0
1291 } ----
1292 } else if (const ConstantExpr *CExpr = dyn_cast(v0)) { 0
1293 const MCExpr *Expr = AP.lowerConstantForGV(cast(CExpr), false); 0
1294 AP.printMCExpr(*Expr, os); 0
1295 } else ----
1296 llvm_unreachable("symbol type unknown"); 0
1297 } 0
1298 ----
1299 void NVPTXAsmPrinter::AggBuffer::printBytes(raw_ostream &os) { 0
1300 unsigned int ptrSize = AP.MAI->getCodePointerSize(); 0
1301 symbolPosInBuffer.push_back(size); 0
1302 unsigned int nSym = 0; 0
1303 unsigned int nextSymbolPos = symbolPosInBuffer[nSym]; 0
1304 for (unsigned int pos = 0; pos < size;) { 0
1305 if (pos) 0
1306 os << ", "; 0
1307 if (pos != nextSymbolPos) { 0
1308 os << (unsigned int)buffer[pos]; 0
1309 ++pos; 0
1310 continue; 0
1311 } ----
1312 // Generate a per-byte mask() operator for the symbol, which looks like: ----
1313 // .global .u8 addr[] = {0xFF(foo), 0xFF00(foo), 0xFF0000(foo), ...}; ----
1314 // See https://docs.nvidia.com/cuda/parallel-thread-execution/index.html#initializers ----
1315 std::string symText; 0
1316 llvm::raw_string_ostream oss(symText); 0
1317 printSymbol(nSym, oss); 0
1318 for (unsigned i = 0; i < ptrSize; ++i) { 0
1319 if (i) 0
1320 os << ", "; 0
1321 llvm::write_hex(os, 0xFFULL << i * 8, HexPrintStyle::PrefixUpper); 0
1322 os << "(" << symText << ")"; 0
1323 } ----
1324 pos += ptrSize; 0
1325 nextSymbolPos = symbolPosInBuffer[++nSym]; 0
1326 assert(nextSymbolPos >= pos); 0
1327 } 0
1328 } 0
1329 ----
1330 void NVPTXAsmPrinter::AggBuffer::printWords(raw_ostream &os) { 0
1331 unsigned int ptrSize = AP.MAI->getCodePointerSize(); 0
1332 symbolPosInBuffer.push_back(size); 0
1333 unsigned int nSym = 0; 0
1334 unsigned int nextSymbolPos = symbolPosInBuffer[nSym]; 0
1335 assert(nextSymbolPos % ptrSize == 0); 0
1336 for (unsigned int pos = 0; pos < size; pos += ptrSize) { 0
1337 if (pos) 0
1338 os << ", "; 0
1339 if (pos == nextSymbolPos) { 0
1340 printSymbol(nSym, os); 0
1341 nextSymbolPos = symbolPosInBuffer[++nSym]; 0
1342 assert(nextSymbolPos % ptrSize == 0); 0
1343 assert(nextSymbolPos >= pos + ptrSize); 0
1344 } else if (ptrSize == 4) 0
1345 os << support::endian::read32le(&buffer[pos]); 0
1346 else ----
1347 os << support::endian::read64le(&buffer[pos]); 0
1348 } ----
1349 } 0
1350 ----
1351 void NVPTXAsmPrinter::emitDemotedVars(const Function *f, raw_ostream &O) { 0
1352 if (localDecls.find(f) == localDecls.end()) 0
1353 return; 0
1354 ----
1355 std::vector &gvars = localDecls[f]; 0
1356 ----
1357 const NVPTXTargetMachine &NTM = static_cast(TM); 0
1358 const NVPTXSubtarget &STI = ----
1359 *static_cast(NTM.getSubtargetImpl()); 0
1360 ----
1361 for (const GlobalVariable *GV : gvars) { 0
1362 O << "\t// demoted variable\n\t"; 0
1363 printModuleLevelGV(GV, O, /*processDemoted=*/true, STI); 0
1364 } ----
1365 } ----
1366 ----
1367 void NVPTXAsmPrinter::emitPTXAddressSpace(unsigned int AddressSpace, 0
1368 raw_ostream &O) const { ----
1369 switch (AddressSpace) { 0
1370 case ADDRESS_SPACE_LOCAL: 0
1371 O << "local"; 0
1372 break; 0
1373 case ADDRESS_SPACE_GLOBAL: 0
1374 O << "global"; 0
1375 break; 0
1376 case ADDRESS_SPACE_CONST: 0
1377 O << "const"; 0
1378 break; 0
1379 case ADDRESS_SPACE_SHARED: 0
1380 O << "shared"; 0
1381 break; 0
1382 default: 0
1383 report_fatal_error("Bad address space found while emitting PTX: " + 0
1384 llvm::Twine(AddressSpace)); 0
1385 break; ----
1386 } ----
1387 } 0
1388 ----
1389 std::string ----
1390 NVPTXAsmPrinter::getPTXFundamentalTypeStr(Type *Ty, bool useB4PTR) const { 0
1391 switch (Ty->getTypeID()) { 0
1392 case Type::IntegerTyID: { 0
1393 unsigned NumBits = cast(Ty)->getBitWidth(); 0
1394 if (NumBits == 1) 0
1395 return "pred"; 0
1396 else if (NumBits <= 64) { 0
1397 std::string name = "u"; 0
1398 return name + utostr(NumBits); 0
1399 } else { 0
1400 llvm_unreachable("Integer too large"); 0
1401 break; ----
1402 } ----
1403 break; ----
1404 } ----
1405 case Type::BFloatTyID: 0
1406 case Type::HalfTyID: ----
1407 // fp16 and bf16 are stored as .b16 for compatibility with pre-sm_53 ----
1408 // PTX assembly. ----
1409 return "b16"; 0
1410 case Type::FloatTyID: 0
1411 return "f32"; 0
1412 case Type::DoubleTyID: 0
1413 return "f64"; 0
1414 case Type::PointerTyID: { 0
1415 unsigned PtrSize = TM.getPointerSizeInBits(Ty->getPointerAddressSpace()); 0
1416 assert((PtrSize == 64 || PtrSize == 32) && "Unexpected pointer size"); 0
1417 ----
1418 if (PtrSize == 64) 0
1419 if (useB4PTR) 0
1420 return "b64"; 0
1421 else ----
1422 return "u64"; 0
1423 else if (useB4PTR) 0
1424 return "b32"; 0
1425 else ----
1426 return "u32"; 0
1427 } ----
1428 default: 0
1429 break; 0
1430 } ----
1431 llvm_unreachable("unexpected type"); 0
1432 } ----
1433 ----
1434 void NVPTXAsmPrinter::emitPTXGlobalVariable(const GlobalVariable *GVar, 0
1435 raw_ostream &O, ----
1436 const NVPTXSubtarget &STI) { ----
1437 const DataLayout &DL = getDataLayout(); 0
1438 ----
1439 // GlobalVariables are always constant pointers themselves. ----
1440 Type *ETy = GVar->getValueType(); 0
1441 ----
1442 O << "."; 0
1443 emitPTXAddressSpace(GVar->getType()->getAddressSpace(), O); 0
1444 if (isManaged(*GVar)) { 0
1445 if (STI.getPTXVersion() < 40 || STI.getSmVersion() < 30) { 0
1446 report_fatal_error( 0
1447 ".attribute(.managed) requires PTX version >= 4.0 and sm_30"); ----
1448 } ----
1449 O << " .attribute(.managed)"; 0
1450 } ----
1451 if (MaybeAlign A = GVar->getAlign()) 0
1452 O << " .align " << A->value(); 0
1453 else ----
1454 O << " .align " << (int)DL.getPrefTypeAlign(ETy).value(); 0
1455 ----
1456 // Special case for i128 ----
1457 if (ETy->isIntegerTy(128)) { 0
1458 O << " .b8 "; 0
1459 getSymbol(GVar)->print(O, MAI); 0
1460 O << "[16]"; 0
1461 return; 0
1462 } ----
1463 ----
1464 if (ETy->isFloatingPointTy() || ETy->isIntOrPtrTy()) { 0
1465 O << " ."; 0
1466 O << getPTXFundamentalTypeStr(ETy); 0
1467 O << " "; 0
1468 getSymbol(GVar)->print(O, MAI); 0
1469 return; 0
1470 } ----
1471 ----
1472 int64_t ElementSize = 0; 0
1473 ----
1474 // Although PTX has direct support for struct type and array type and LLVM IR ----
1475 // is very similar to PTX, the LLVM CodeGen does not support for targets that ----
1476 // support these high level field accesses. Structs and arrays are lowered ----
1477 // into arrays of bytes. ----
1478 switch (ETy->getTypeID()) { 0
1479 case Type::StructTyID: 0
1480 case Type::ArrayTyID: ----
1481 case Type::FixedVectorTyID: ----
1482 ElementSize = DL.getTypeStoreSize(ETy); 0
1483 O << " .b8 "; 0
1484 getSymbol(GVar)->print(O, MAI); 0
1485 O << "["; 0
1486 if (ElementSize) { 0
1487 O << ElementSize; 0
1488 } ----
1489 O << "]"; 0
1490 break; 0
1491 default: 0
1492 llvm_unreachable("type not supported yet"); 0
1493 } ----
1494 } ----
1495 ----
1496 void NVPTXAsmPrinter::emitFunctionParamList(const Function *F, raw_ostream &O) { 0
1497 const DataLayout &DL = getDataLayout(); 0
1498 const AttributeList &PAL = F->getAttributes(); 0
1499 const NVPTXSubtarget &STI = TM.getSubtarget(*F); 0
1500 const auto *TLI = cast(STI.getTargetLowering()); 0
1501 ----
1502 Function::const_arg_iterator I, E; ----
1503 unsigned paramIndex = 0; 0
1504 bool first = true; 0
1505 bool isKernelFunc = isKernelFunction(*F); 0
1506 bool isABI = (STI.getSmVersion() >= 20); 0
1507 bool hasImageHandles = STI.hasImageHandles(); 0
1508 ----
1509 if (F->arg_empty() && !F->isVarArg()) { 0
1510 O << "()"; 0
1511 return; 0
1512 } ----
1513 ----
1514 O << "(\n"; 0
1515 ----
1516 for (I = F->arg_begin(), E = F->arg_end(); I != E; ++I, paramIndex++) { 0
1517 Type *Ty = I->getType(); 0
1518 ----
1519 if (!first) 0
1520 O << ",\n"; 0
1521 ----
1522 first = false; 0
1523 ----
1524 // Handle image/sampler parameters ----
1525 if (isKernelFunction(*F)) { 0
1526 if (isSampler(*I) || isImage(*I)) { 0
1527 if (isImage(*I)) { 0
1528 std::string sname = std::string(I->getName()); 0
1529 if (isImageWriteOnly(*I) || isImageReadWrite(*I)) { 0
1530 if (hasImageHandles) 0
1531 O << "\t.param .u64 .ptr .surfref "; 0
1532 else ----
1533 O << "\t.param .surfref "; 0
1534 O << TLI->getParamName(F, paramIndex); 0
1535 } ----
1536 else { // Default image is read_only ----
1537 if (hasImageHandles) 0
1538 O << "\t.param .u64 .ptr .texref "; 0
1539 else ----
1540 O << "\t.param .texref "; 0
1541 O << TLI->getParamName(F, paramIndex); 0
1542 } ----
1543 } else { 0
1544 if (hasImageHandles) 0
1545 O << "\t.param .u64 .ptr .samplerref "; 0
1546 else ----
1547 O << "\t.param .samplerref "; 0
1548 O << TLI->getParamName(F, paramIndex); 0
1549 } ----
1550 continue; 0
1551 } 0
1552 } ----
1553 ----
1554 auto getOptimalAlignForParam = [TLI, &DL, &PAL, F, 0
1555 paramIndex](Type *Ty) -> Align { 0
1556 Align TypeAlign = TLI->getFunctionParamOptimizedAlign(F, Ty, DL); 0
1557 MaybeAlign ParamAlign = PAL.getParamAlignment(paramIndex); 0
1558 return std::max(TypeAlign, ParamAlign.valueOrOne()); 0
1559 }; 0
1560 ----
1561 if (!PAL.hasParamAttr(paramIndex, Attribute::ByVal)) { 0
1562 if (ShouldPassAsArray(Ty)) { 0
1563 // Just print .param .align .b8 .param[size]; ----
1564 // = optimal alignment for the element type; always multiple of ----
1565 // PAL.getParamAlignment ----
1566 // size = typeallocsize of element type ----
1567 Align OptimalAlign = getOptimalAlignForParam(Ty); 0
1568 ----
1569 O << "\t.param .align " << OptimalAlign.value() << " .b8 "; 0
1570 O << TLI->getParamName(F, paramIndex); 0
1571 O << "[" << DL.getTypeAllocSize(Ty) << "]"; 0
1572 ----
1573 continue; 0
1574 } 0
1575 // Just a scalar ----
1576 auto *PTy = dyn_cast(Ty); 0
1577 unsigned PTySizeInBits = 0; 0
1578 if (PTy) { 0
1579 PTySizeInBits = 0
1580 TLI->getPointerTy(DL, PTy->getAddressSpace()).getSizeInBits(); 0
1581 assert(PTySizeInBits && "Invalid pointer size"); 0
1582 } ----
1583 ----
1584 if (isKernelFunc) { 0
1585 if (PTy) { 0
1586 // Special handling for pointer arguments to kernel ----
1587 O << "\t.param .u" << PTySizeInBits << " "; 0
1588 ----
1589 if (static_cast(TM).getDrvInterface() != 0
1590 NVPTX::CUDA) { ----
1591 int addrSpace = PTy->getAddressSpace(); 0
1592 switch (addrSpace) { 0
1593 default: 0
1594 O << ".ptr "; 0
1595 break; 0
1596 case ADDRESS_SPACE_CONST: 0
1597 O << ".ptr .const "; 0
1598 break; 0
1599 case ADDRESS_SPACE_SHARED: 0
1600 O << ".ptr .shared "; 0
1601 break; 0
1602 case ADDRESS_SPACE_GLOBAL: 0
1603 O << ".ptr .global "; 0
1604 break; 0
1605 } ----
1606 Align ParamAlign = I->getParamAlign().valueOrOne(); 0
1607 O << ".align " << ParamAlign.value() << " "; 0
1608 } ----
1609 O << TLI->getParamName(F, paramIndex); 0
1610 continue; 0
1611 } 0
1612 ----
1613 // non-pointer scalar to kernel func ----
1614 O << "\t.param ."; 0
1615 // Special case: predicate operands become .u8 types ----
1616 if (Ty->isIntegerTy(1)) 0
1617 O << "u8"; 0
1618 else ----
1619 O << getPTXFundamentalTypeStr(Ty); 0
1620 O << " "; 0
1621 O << TLI->getParamName(F, paramIndex); 0
1622 continue; 0
1623 } 0
1624 // Non-kernel function, just print .param .b for ABI ----
1625 // and .reg .b for non-ABI ----
1626 unsigned sz = 0; 0
1627 if (isa(Ty)) { 0
1628 sz = cast(Ty)->getBitWidth(); 0
1629 sz = promoteScalarArgumentSize(sz); 0
1630 } else if (PTy) { 0
1631 assert(PTySizeInBits && "Invalid pointer size"); 0
1632 sz = PTySizeInBits; 0
1633 } else ----
1634 sz = Ty->getPrimitiveSizeInBits(); 0
1635 if (isABI) 0
1636 O << "\t.param .b" << sz << " "; 0
1637 else ----
1638 O << "\t.reg .b" << sz << " "; 0
1639 O << TLI->getParamName(F, paramIndex); 0
1640 continue; 0
1641 } 0
1642 ----
1643 // param has byVal attribute. ----
1644 Type *ETy = PAL.getParamByValType(paramIndex); 0
1645 assert(ETy && "Param should have byval type"); 0
1646 ----
1647 if (isABI || isKernelFunc) { 0
1648 // Just print .param .align .b8 .param[size]; ----
1649 // = optimal alignment for the element type; always multiple of ----
1650 // PAL.getParamAlignment ----
1651 // size = typeallocsize of element type ----
1652 Align OptimalAlign = ----
1653 isKernelFunc ----
1654 ? getOptimalAlignForParam(ETy) 0
1655 : TLI->getFunctionByValParamAlign( 0
1656 F, ETy, PAL.getParamAlignment(paramIndex).valueOrOne(), DL); 0
1657 ----
1658 unsigned sz = DL.getTypeAllocSize(ETy); 0
1659 O << "\t.param .align " << OptimalAlign.value() << " .b8 "; 0
1660 O << TLI->getParamName(F, paramIndex); 0
1661 O << "[" << sz << "]"; 0
1662 continue; 0
1663 } else { 0
1664 // Split the ETy into constituent parts and ----
1665 // print .param .b for each part. ----
1666 // Further, if a part is vector, print the above for ----
1667 // each vector element. ----
1668 SmallVector vtparts; 0
1669 ComputeValueVTs(*TLI, DL, ETy, vtparts); 0
1670 for (unsigned i = 0, e = vtparts.size(); i != e; ++i) { 0
1671 unsigned elems = 1; 0
1672 EVT elemtype = vtparts[i]; 0
1673 if (vtparts[i].isVector()) { 0
1674 elems = vtparts[i].getVectorNumElements(); 0
1675 elemtype = vtparts[i].getVectorElementType(); 0
1676 } ----
1677 ----
1678 for (unsigned j = 0, je = elems; j != je; ++j) { 0
1679 unsigned sz = elemtype.getSizeInBits(); 0
1680 if (elemtype.isInteger()) 0
1681 sz = promoteScalarArgumentSize(sz); 0
1682 O << "\t.reg .b" << sz << " "; 0
1683 O << TLI->getParamName(F, paramIndex); 0
1684 if (j < je - 1) 0
1685 O << ",\n"; 0
1686 ++paramIndex; 0
1687 } ----
1688 if (i < e - 1) 0
1689 O << ",\n"; 0
1690 } ----
1691 --paramIndex; 0
1692 continue; 0
1693 } 0
1694 } ----
1695 ----
1696 if (F->isVarArg()) { 0
1697 if (!first) 0
1698 O << ",\n"; 0
1699 O << "\t.param .align " << STI.getMaxRequiredAlignment(); 0
1700 O << " .b8 "; 0
1701 O << TLI->getParamName(F, /* vararg */ -1) << "[]"; 0
1702 } ----
1703 ----
1704 O << "\n)"; 0
1705 } ----
1706 ----
1707 void NVPTXAsmPrinter::setAndEmitFunctionVirtualRegisters( 0
1708 const MachineFunction &MF) { ----
1709 SmallString<128> Str; 0
1710 raw_svector_ostream O(Str); 0
1711 ----
1712 // Map the global virtual register number to a register class specific ----
1713 // virtual register number starting from 1 with that class. ----
1714 const TargetRegisterInfo *TRI = MF.getSubtarget().getRegisterInfo(); 0
1715 //unsigned numRegClasses = TRI->getNumRegClasses(); ----
1716 ----
1717 // Emit the Fake Stack Object ----
1718 const MachineFrameInfo &MFI = MF.getFrameInfo(); 0
1719 int NumBytes = (int) MFI.getStackSize(); 0
1720 if (NumBytes) { 0
1721 O << "\t.local .align " << MFI.getMaxAlign().value() << " .b8 \t" 0
1722 << DEPOTNAME << getFunctionNumber() << "[" << NumBytes << "];\n"; 0
1723 if (static_cast(MF.getTarget()).is64Bit()) { 0
1724 O << "\t.reg .b64 \t%SP;\n"; 0
1725 O << "\t.reg .b64 \t%SPL;\n"; 0
1726 } else { ----
1727 O << "\t.reg .b32 \t%SP;\n"; 0
1728 O << "\t.reg .b32 \t%SPL;\n"; 0
1729 } ----
1730 } ----
1731 ----
1732 // Go through all virtual registers to establish the mapping between the ----
1733 // global virtual ----
1734 // register number and the per class virtual register number. ----
1735 // We use the per class virtual register number in the ptx output. ----
1736 unsigned int numVRs = MRI->getNumVirtRegs(); 0
1737 for (unsigned i = 0; i < numVRs; i++) { 0
1738 Register vr = Register::index2VirtReg(i); 0
1739 const TargetRegisterClass *RC = MRI->getRegClass(vr); 0
1740 DenseMap ®map = VRegMapping[RC]; 0
1741 int n = regmap.size(); 0
1742 regmap.insert(std::make_pair(vr, n + 1)); 0
1743 } ----
1744 ----
1745 // Emit register declarations ----
1746 // @TODO: Extract out the real register usage ----
1747 // O << "\t.reg .pred %p<" << NVPTXNumRegisters << ">;\n"; ----
1748 // O << "\t.reg .s16 %rc<" << NVPTXNumRegisters << ">;\n"; ----
1749 // O << "\t.reg .s16 %rs<" << NVPTXNumRegisters << ">;\n"; ----
1750 // O << "\t.reg .s32 %r<" << NVPTXNumRegisters << ">;\n"; ----
1751 // O << "\t.reg .s64 %rd<" << NVPTXNumRegisters << ">;\n"; ----
1752 // O << "\t.reg .f32 %f<" << NVPTXNumRegisters << ">;\n"; ----
1753 // O << "\t.reg .f64 %fd<" << NVPTXNumRegisters << ">;\n"; ----
1754 ----
1755 // Emit declaration of the virtual registers or 'physical' registers for ----
1756 // each register class ----
1757 for (unsigned i=0; i< TRI->getNumRegClasses(); i++) { 0
1758 const TargetRegisterClass *RC = TRI->getRegClass(i); 0
1759 DenseMap ®map = VRegMapping[RC]; 0
1760 std::string rcname = getNVPTXRegClassName(RC); 0
1761 std::string rcStr = getNVPTXRegClassStr(RC); 0
1762 int n = regmap.size(); 0
1763 ----
1764 // Only declare those registers that may be used. ----
1765 if (n) { 0
1766 O << "\t.reg " << rcname << " \t" << rcStr << "<" << (n+1) 0
1767 << ">;\n"; 0
1768 } ----
1769 } 0
1770 ----
1771 OutStreamer->emitRawText(O.str()); 0
1772 } 0
1773 ----
1774 void NVPTXAsmPrinter::printFPConstant(const ConstantFP *Fp, raw_ostream &O) { 0
1775 APFloat APF = APFloat(Fp->getValueAPF()); // make a copy 0
1776 bool ignored; ----
1777 unsigned int numHex; ----
1778 const char *lead; ----
1779 ----
1780 if (Fp->getType()->getTypeID() == Type::FloatTyID) { 0
1781 numHex = 8; 0
1782 lead = "0f"; 0
1783 APF.convert(APFloat::IEEEsingle(), APFloat::rmNearestTiesToEven, &ignored); 0
1784 } else if (Fp->getType()->getTypeID() == Type::DoubleTyID) { 0
1785 numHex = 16; 0
1786 lead = "0d"; 0
1787 APF.convert(APFloat::IEEEdouble(), APFloat::rmNearestTiesToEven, &ignored); 0
1788 } else ----
1789 llvm_unreachable("unsupported fp type"); 0
1790 ----
1791 APInt API = APF.bitcastToAPInt(); 0
1792 O << lead << format_hex_no_prefix(API.getZExtValue(), numHex, /*Upper=*/true); 0
1793 } 0
1794 ----
1795 void NVPTXAsmPrinter::printScalarConstant(const Constant *CPV, raw_ostream &O) { 0
1796 if (const ConstantInt *CI = dyn_cast(CPV)) { 0
1797 O << CI->getValue(); 0
1798 return; 0
1799 } ----
1800 if (const ConstantFP *CFP = dyn_cast(CPV)) { 0
1801 printFPConstant(CFP, O); 0
1802 return; 0
1803 } ----
1804 if (isa(CPV)) { 0
1805 O << "0"; 0
1806 return; 0
1807 } ----
1808 if (const GlobalValue *GVar = dyn_cast(CPV)) { 0
1809 bool IsNonGenericPointer = false; 0
1810 if (GVar->getType()->getAddressSpace() != 0) { 0
1811 IsNonGenericPointer = true; 0
1812 } ----
1813 if (EmitGeneric && !isa(CPV) && !IsNonGenericPointer) { 0
1814 O << "generic("; 0
1815 getSymbol(GVar)->print(O, MAI); 0
1816 O << ")"; 0
1817 } else { ----
1818 getSymbol(GVar)->print(O, MAI); 0
1819 } ----
1820 return; 0
1821 } ----
1822 if (const ConstantExpr *Cexpr = dyn_cast(CPV)) { 0
1823 const MCExpr *E = lowerConstantForGV(cast(Cexpr), false); 0
1824 printMCExpr(*E, O); 0
1825 return; 0
1826 } ----
1827 llvm_unreachable("Not scalar type found in printScalarConstant()"); 0
1828 } ----
1829 ----
1830 void NVPTXAsmPrinter::bufferLEByte(const Constant *CPV, int Bytes, 0
1831 AggBuffer *AggBuffer) { ----
1832 const DataLayout &DL = getDataLayout(); 0
1833 int AllocSize = DL.getTypeAllocSize(CPV->getType()); 0
1834 if (isa(CPV) || CPV->isNullValue()) { 0
1835 // Non-zero Bytes indicates that we need to zero-fill everything. Otherwise, ----
1836 // only the space allocated by CPV. ----
1837 AggBuffer->addZeros(Bytes ? Bytes : AllocSize); 0
1838 return; 0
1839 } ----
1840 ----
1841 // Helper for filling AggBuffer with APInts. ----
1842 auto AddIntToBuffer = [AggBuffer, Bytes](const APInt &Val) { 0
1843 size_t NumBytes = (Val.getBitWidth() + 7) / 8; 0
1844 SmallVector Buf(NumBytes); 0
1845 for (unsigned I = 0; I < NumBytes; ++I) { 0
1846 Buf[I] = Val.extractBitsAsZExtValue(8, I * 8); 0
1847 } ----
1848 AggBuffer->addBytes(Buf.data(), NumBytes, Bytes); 0
1849 }; 0
1850 ----
1851 switch (CPV->getType()->getTypeID()) { 0
1852 case Type::IntegerTyID: 0
1853 if (const auto CI = dyn_cast(CPV)) { 0
1854 AddIntToBuffer(CI->getValue()); 0
1855 break; 0
1856 } ----
1857 if (const auto *Cexpr = dyn_cast(CPV)) { 0
1858 if (const auto *CI = 0
1859 dyn_cast(ConstantFoldConstant(Cexpr, DL))) { 0
1860 AddIntToBuffer(CI->getValue()); 0
1861 break; 0
1862 } ----
1863 if (Cexpr->getOpcode() == Instruction::PtrToInt) { 0
1864 Value *V = Cexpr->getOperand(0)->stripPointerCasts(); 0
1865 AggBuffer->addSymbol(V, Cexpr->getOperand(0)); 0
1866 AggBuffer->addZeros(AllocSize); 0
1867 break; 0
1868 } ----
1869 } ----
1870 llvm_unreachable("unsupported integer const type"); 0
1871 break; ----
1872 ----
1873 case Type::HalfTyID: 0
1874 case Type::BFloatTyID: ----
1875 case Type::FloatTyID: ----
1876 case Type::DoubleTyID: ----
1877 AddIntToBuffer(cast(CPV)->getValueAPF().bitcastToAPInt()); 0
1878 break; 0
1879 ----
1880 case Type::PointerTyID: { 0
1881 if (const GlobalValue *GVar = dyn_cast(CPV)) { 0
1882 AggBuffer->addSymbol(GVar, GVar); 0
1883 } else if (const ConstantExpr *Cexpr = dyn_cast(CPV)) { 0
1884 const Value *v = Cexpr->stripPointerCasts(); 0
1885 AggBuffer->addSymbol(v, Cexpr); 0
1886 } ----
1887 AggBuffer->addZeros(AllocSize); 0
1888 break; 0
1889 } ----
1890 ----
1891 case Type::ArrayTyID: 0
1892 case Type::FixedVectorTyID: ----
1893 case Type::StructTyID: { ----
1894 if (isa(CPV) || isa(CPV)) { 0
1895 bufferAggregateConstant(CPV, AggBuffer); 0
1896 if (Bytes > AllocSize) 0
1897 AggBuffer->addZeros(Bytes - AllocSize); 0
1898 } else if (isa(CPV)) 0
1899 AggBuffer->addZeros(Bytes); 0
1900 else ----
1901 llvm_unreachable("Unexpected Constant type"); 0
1902 break; 0
1903 } ----
1904 ----
1905 default: 0
1906 llvm_unreachable("unsupported type"); 0
1907 } ----
1908 } ----
1909 ----
1910 void NVPTXAsmPrinter::bufferAggregateConstant(const Constant *CPV, 0
1911 AggBuffer *aggBuffer) { ----
1912 const DataLayout &DL = getDataLayout(); 0
1913 int Bytes; ----
1914 ----
1915 // Integers of arbitrary width ----
1916 if (const ConstantInt *CI = dyn_cast(CPV)) { 0
1917 APInt Val = CI->getValue(); 0
1918 for (unsigned I = 0, E = DL.getTypeAllocSize(CPV->getType()); I < E; ++I) { 0
1919 uint8_t Byte = Val.getLoBits(8).getZExtValue(); 0
1920 aggBuffer->addBytes(&Byte, 1, 1); 0
1921 Val.lshrInPlace(8); 0
1922 } ----
1923 return; 0
1924 } 0
1925 ----
1926 // Old constants ----
1927 if (isa(CPV) || isa(CPV)) { 0
1928 if (CPV->getNumOperands()) 0
1929 for (unsigned i = 0, e = CPV->getNumOperands(); i != e; ++i) 0
1930 bufferLEByte(cast(CPV->getOperand(i)), 0, aggBuffer); 0
1931 return; 0
1932 } ----
1933 ----
1934 if (const ConstantDataSequential *CDS = 0
1935 dyn_cast(CPV)) { 0
1936 if (CDS->getNumElements()) 0
1937 for (unsigned i = 0; i < CDS->getNumElements(); ++i) 0
1938 bufferLEByte(cast(CDS->getElementAsConstant(i)), 0, 0
1939 aggBuffer); ----
1940 return; 0
1941 } ----
1942 ----
1943 if (isa(CPV)) { 0
1944 if (CPV->getNumOperands()) { 0
1945 StructType *ST = cast(CPV->getType()); 0
1946 for (unsigned i = 0, e = CPV->getNumOperands(); i != e; ++i) { 0
1947 if (i == (e - 1)) 0
1948 Bytes = DL.getStructLayout(ST)->getElementOffset(0) + 0
1949 DL.getTypeAllocSize(ST) - 0
1950 DL.getStructLayout(ST)->getElementOffset(i); 0
1951 else ----
1952 Bytes = DL.getStructLayout(ST)->getElementOffset(i + 1) - 0
1953 DL.getStructLayout(ST)->getElementOffset(i); 0
1954 bufferLEByte(cast(CPV->getOperand(i)), Bytes, aggBuffer); 0
1955 } ----
1956 } ----
1957 return; 0
1958 } ----
1959 llvm_unreachable("unsupported constant type in printAggregateConstant()"); 0
1960 } ----
1961 ----
1962 /// lowerConstantForGV - Return an MCExpr for the given Constant. This is mostly ----
1963 /// a copy from AsmPrinter::lowerConstant, except customized to only handle ----
1964 /// expressions that are representable in PTX and create ----
1965 /// NVPTXGenericMCSymbolRefExpr nodes for addrspacecast instructions. ----
1966 const MCExpr * ----
1967 NVPTXAsmPrinter::lowerConstantForGV(const Constant *CV, bool ProcessingGeneric) { 0
1968 MCContext &Ctx = OutContext; 0
1969 ----
1970 if (CV->isNullValue() || isa(CV)) 0
1971 return MCConstantExpr::create(0, Ctx); 0
1972 ----
1973 if (const ConstantInt *CI = dyn_cast(CV)) 0
1974 return MCConstantExpr::create(CI->getZExtValue(), Ctx); 0
1975 ----
1976 if (const GlobalValue *GV = dyn_cast(CV)) { 0
1977 const MCSymbolRefExpr *Expr = ----
1978 MCSymbolRefExpr::create(getSymbol(GV), Ctx); 0
1979 if (ProcessingGeneric) { 0
1980 return NVPTXGenericMCSymbolRefExpr::create(Expr, Ctx); 0
1981 } else { ----
1982 return Expr; 0
1983 } ----
1984 } ----
1985 ----
1986 const ConstantExpr *CE = dyn_cast(CV); 0
1987 if (!CE) { 0
1988 llvm_unreachable("Unknown constant value to lower!"); 0
1989 } ----
1990 ----
1991 switch (CE->getOpcode()) { 0
1992 default: { 0
1993 // If the code isn't optimized, there may be outstanding folding ----
1994 // opportunities. Attempt to fold the expression using DataLayout as a ----
1995 // last resort before giving up. ----
1996 Constant *C = ConstantFoldConstant(CE, getDataLayout()); 0
1997 if (C != CE) 0
1998 return lowerConstantForGV(C, ProcessingGeneric); 0
1999 ----
2000 // Otherwise report the problem to the user. ----
2001 std::string S; 0
2002 raw_string_ostream OS(S); 0
2003 OS << "Unsupported expression in static initializer: "; 0
2004 CE->printAsOperand(OS, /*PrintType=*/false, 0
2005 !MF ? nullptr : MF->getFunction().getParent()); 0
2006 report_fatal_error(Twine(OS.str())); 0
2007 } ----
2008 ----
2009 case Instruction::AddrSpaceCast: { 0
2010 // Strip the addrspacecast and pass along the operand ----
2011 PointerType *DstTy = cast(CE->getType()); 0
2012 if (DstTy->getAddressSpace() == 0) { 0
2013 return lowerConstantForGV(cast(CE->getOperand(0)), true); 0
2014 } ----
2015 std::string S; 0
2016 raw_string_ostream OS(S); 0
2017 OS << "Unsupported expression in static initializer: "; 0
2018 CE->printAsOperand(OS, /*PrintType=*/ false, 0
2019 !MF ? nullptr : MF->getFunction().getParent()); 0
2020 report_fatal_error(Twine(OS.str())); 0
2021 } ----
2022 ----
2023 case Instruction::GetElementPtr: { 0
2024 const DataLayout &DL = getDataLayout(); 0
2025 ----
2026 // Generate a symbolic expression for the byte address ----
2027 APInt OffsetAI(DL.getPointerTypeSizeInBits(CE->getType()), 0); 0
2028 cast(CE)->accumulateConstantOffset(DL, OffsetAI); 0
2029 ----
2030 const MCExpr *Base = lowerConstantForGV(CE->getOperand(0), 0
2031 ProcessingGeneric); ----
2032 if (!OffsetAI) 0
2033 return Base; 0
2034 ----
2035 int64_t Offset = OffsetAI.getSExtValue(); 0
2036 return MCBinaryExpr::createAdd(Base, MCConstantExpr::create(Offset, Ctx), 0
2037 Ctx); 0
2038 } 0
2039 ----
2040 case Instruction::Trunc: 0
2041 // We emit the value and depend on the assembler to truncate the generated ----
2042 // expression properly. This is important for differences between ----
2043 // blockaddress labels. Since the two labels are in the same function, it ----
2044 // is reasonable to treat their delta as a 32-bit value. ----
2045 [[fallthrough]]; ----
2046 case Instruction::BitCast: ----
2047 return lowerConstantForGV(CE->getOperand(0), ProcessingGeneric); 0
2048 ----
2049 case Instruction::IntToPtr: { 0
2050 const DataLayout &DL = getDataLayout(); 0
2051 ----
2052 // Handle casts to pointers by changing them into casts to the appropriate ----
2053 // integer type. This promotes constant folding and simplifies this code. ----
2054 Constant *Op = CE->getOperand(0); 0
2055 Op = ConstantExpr::getIntegerCast(Op, DL.getIntPtrType(CV->getType()), 0
2056 false/*ZExt*/); ----
2057 return lowerConstantForGV(Op, ProcessingGeneric); 0
2058 } ----
2059 ----
2060 case Instruction::PtrToInt: { 0
2061 const DataLayout &DL = getDataLayout(); 0
2062 ----
2063 // Support only foldable casts to/from pointers that can be eliminated by ----
2064 // changing the pointer to the appropriately sized integer type. ----
2065 Constant *Op = CE->getOperand(0); 0
2066 Type *Ty = CE->getType(); 0
2067 ----
2068 const MCExpr *OpExpr = lowerConstantForGV(Op, ProcessingGeneric); 0
2069 ----
2070 // We can emit the pointer value into this slot if the slot is an ----
2071 // integer slot equal to the size of the pointer. ----
2072 if (DL.getTypeAllocSize(Ty) == DL.getTypeAllocSize(Op->getType())) 0
2073 return OpExpr; 0
2074 ----
2075 // Otherwise the pointer is smaller than the resultant integer, mask off ----
2076 // the high bits so we are sure to get a proper truncation if the input is ----
2077 // a constant expr. ----
2078 unsigned InBits = DL.getTypeAllocSizeInBits(Op->getType()); 0
2079 const MCExpr *MaskExpr = MCConstantExpr::create(~0ULL >> (64-InBits), Ctx); 0
2080 return MCBinaryExpr::createAnd(OpExpr, MaskExpr, Ctx); 0
2081 } ----
2082 ----
2083 // The MC library also has a right-shift operator, but it isn't consistently ----
2084 // signed or unsigned between different targets. ----
2085 case Instruction::Add: { 0
2086 const MCExpr *LHS = lowerConstantForGV(CE->getOperand(0), ProcessingGeneric); 0
2087 const MCExpr *RHS = lowerConstantForGV(CE->getOperand(1), ProcessingGeneric); 0
2088 switch (CE->getOpcode()) { 0
2089 default: llvm_unreachable("Unknown binary operator constant cast expr"); 0
2090 case Instruction::Add: return MCBinaryExpr::createAdd(LHS, RHS, Ctx); 0
2091 } ----
2092 } ----
2093 } ----
2094 } ----

2096 // Copy of MCExpr::print customized for NVPTX ----
2097 void NVPTXAsmPrinter::printMCExpr(const MCExpr &Expr, raw_ostream &OS) { 0
2098 switch (Expr.getKind()) { 0
2099 case MCExpr::Target: 0
2100 return cast(&Expr)->printImpl(OS, MAI); 0
2101 case MCExpr::Constant: 0
2102 OS << cast(Expr).getValue(); 0
2103 return; 0
2104 ----
2105 case MCExpr::SymbolRef: { 0
2106 const MCSymbolRefExpr &SRE = cast(Expr); 0
2107 const MCSymbol &Sym = SRE.getSymbol(); 0
2108 Sym.print(OS, MAI); 0
2109 return; 0
2110 } ----
2111 ----
2112 case MCExpr::Unary: { 0
2113 const MCUnaryExpr &UE = cast(Expr); 0
2114 switch (UE.getOpcode()) { 0
2115 case MCUnaryExpr::LNot: OS << '!'; break; 0
2116 case MCUnaryExpr::Minus: OS << '-'; break; 0
2117 case MCUnaryExpr::Not: OS << '~'; break; 0
2118 case MCUnaryExpr::Plus: OS << '+'; break; 0
2119 } ----
2120 printMCExpr(*UE.getSubExpr(), OS); 0
2121 return; 0
2122 } ----
2123 ----
2124 case MCExpr::Binary: { 0
2125 const MCBinaryExpr &BE = cast(Expr); 0
2126 ----
2127 // Only print parens around the LHS if it is non-trivial. ----
2128 if (isa(BE.getLHS()) || isa(BE.getLHS()) || 0
2129 isa(BE.getLHS())) { 0
2130 printMCExpr(*BE.getLHS(), OS); 0
2131 } else { ----
2132 OS << '('; 0
2133 printMCExpr(*BE.getLHS(), OS); 0
2134 OS<< ')'; 0
2135 } ----
2136 ----
2137 switch (BE.getOpcode()) { 0
2138 case MCBinaryExpr::Add: 0
2139 // Print "X-42" instead of "X+-42". ----
2140 if (const MCConstantExpr *RHSC = dyn_cast(BE.getRHS())) { 0
2141 if (RHSC->getValue() < 0) { 0
2142 OS << RHSC->getValue(); 0
2143 return; 0
2144 } ----
2145 } ----
2146 ----
2147 OS << '+'; 0
2148 break; 0
2149 default: llvm_unreachable("Unhandled binary operator"); 0
2150 } ----
2151 ----
2152 // Only print parens around the LHS if it is non-trivial. ----
2153 if (isa(BE.getRHS()) || isa(BE.getRHS())) { 0
2154 printMCExpr(*BE.getRHS(), OS); 0
2155 } else { ----
2156 OS << '('; 0
2157 printMCExpr(*BE.getRHS(), OS); 0
2158 OS << ')'; 0
2159 } ----
2160 return; 0
2161 } ----
2162 } ----
2163 ----
2164 llvm_unreachable("Invalid expression kind!"); 0
2165 } ----

102 /// DiscoverDependentGlobals - Return a set of GlobalVariables on which \p V 102 /// DiscoverDependentGlobals - Return a set of GlobalVariables on which \p V
103 /// depends. 103 /// depends.
104 static void 104 static void
105 DiscoverDependentGlobals(const Value *V, 105 DiscoverDependentGlobals(const Value *V,
106 DenseSet &Globals) { 106 DenseSet &Globals) {
107 if (const GlobalVariable *GV = dyn_cast(V)) 107 if (const GlobalVariable *GV = dyn_cast(V))
108 Globals.insert(GV); 108 Globals.insert(GV);
109 else { 109 else {
110 if (const User *U = dyn_cast(V)) { 110 if (const User *U = dyn_cast(V)) {
111 for (unsigned i = 0, e = U->getNumOperands(); i != e; ++i) { 111 for (unsigned i = 0, e = U->getNumOperands(); i != e; ++i) {
112 DiscoverDependentGlobals(U->getOperand(i), Globals); 112 DiscoverDependentGlobals(U->getOperand(i), Globals);
113 } 113 }
114 } 114 }
115 } 115 }
116 } 116 }

118 /// VisitGlobalVariableForEmission - Add \p GV to the list of GlobalVariable 118 /// VisitGlobalVariableForEmission - Add \p GV to the list of GlobalVariable
119 /// instances to be emitted, but only after any dependents have been added 119 /// instances to be emitted, but only after any dependents have been added
120 /// first.s 120 /// first.s
121 static void 121 static void
122 VisitGlobalVariableForEmission(const GlobalVariable *GV, 122 VisitGlobalVariableForEmission(const GlobalVariable *GV,
123 SmallVectorImpl &Order, 123 SmallVectorImpl &Order,
124 DenseSet &Visited, 124 DenseSet &Visited,
125 DenseSet &Visiting) { 125 DenseSet &Visiting) {
126 // Have we already visited this one? 126 // Have we already visited this one?
127 if (Visited.count(GV)) 127 if (Visited.count(GV))
128 return; 128 return;
129 129
130 // Do we have a circular dependency? 130 // Do we have a circular dependency?
131 if (!Visiting.insert(GV).second) 131 if (!Visiting.insert(GV).second)
132 report_fatal_error("Circular dependency found in global variable set"); 132 report_fatal_error("Circular dependency found in global variable set");
133 133
134 // Make sure we visit all dependents first 134 // Make sure we visit all dependents first
135 DenseSet Others; 135 DenseSet Others;
136 for (unsigned i = 0, e = GV->getNumOperands(); i != e; ++i) 136 for (unsigned i = 0, e = GV->getNumOperands(); i != e; ++i)
137 DiscoverDependentGlobals(GV->getOperand(i), Others); 137 DiscoverDependentGlobals(GV->getOperand(i), Others);
138 138
139 for (const GlobalVariable *GV : Others) 139 for (const GlobalVariable *GV : Others)
140 VisitGlobalVariableForEmission(GV, Order, Visited, Visiting); 140 VisitGlobalVariableForEmission(GV, Order, Visited, Visiting);
141 141
142 // Now we can visit ourself 142 // Now we can visit ourself
143 Order.push_back(GV); 143 Order.push_back(GV);
144 Visited.insert(GV); 144 Visited.insert(GV);
145 Visiting.erase(GV); 145 Visiting.erase(GV);
146 } 146 }
